➜2020年11月大学英语六级口语考试第九场个人陈述-校园停放车辆
http://www.sohu.com/a/433563416_100684	12755
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p0.itc.cn/images01/20201122/145c27d3b2bc4c1d952dd142af26793a.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>本场的个人陈述话题是：校园里应不应该停放车辆，以及对校园里停放越来越多的车辆有什么看法。这个话题非常贴近生活，有很多内容可谈。考生只需把自己的观点陈述出来，逻辑清晰即可。下面是一篇范文，供各位考生参考。</p>
<p>Nowadays, there are a lot of such phenomena on campus: a lot of private cars parked on the roads, which brings great inconvenience to students and teachers. So should cars be parked on campus? As far as I am concerned, first, there should be fixed parking spaces on campus and car owners should park their cars on them. Second, if a car owner misplaces the car, which affects the travel of students and teachers, the university should investigate the severity and impose a fine. This would encourage owners to put their cars in the right places and penalize those who leave them in the wrong places. In addition, unregistered vehicles are prohibited from entering the campus. These vehicles will not only affect the campus environment, but also threaten the safety of students. In a word, the campus is a place for students who need a clean environment and quiet atmosphere to ensure that they are fully engaged in their study. Therefore, the problem of disorderly parking needs to be dealt with seriously.</p>
<p>以上就是<strong>文都四六级英语</strong>老师为各位考生带来的六级口语考试第九场个人陈述部分的参考范本，希望能够对各位考生有所帮助。最后，<strong>文都教育</strong>祝各位同学都可以取得令人满意的成绩</p>
➜2020年11月大学英语六级口语考试真题第八场——克服孤独
http://www.sohu.com/a/433562733_100684	12762
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p9.itc.cn/images01/20201122/246819c641e0456489043470be1c36c1.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>2020年11月22日，大学英语六级口语考试如期举行。大学英语六级口语考试共分三个环节进行考查，第一个环节是自我介绍和问答，第二个环节是个人陈述和互动讨论，第三个环节是问答。本场互动讨论的话题为“克服孤独”。在人的一生中，总有孤独失意的时候，对自己的人际交往找不到自信。人是群居动物，所以绝大数的人还是喜欢有人陪伴。一个人的孤独是痛苦的，因为你没有可以分享你感受的人。那么该怎么克服孤独呢？下面是文都六级英语老师围绕这一话题给出的相关对话表述，供同学们学习参考。</p>
<p>【讨论话题】</p>
<p>克服孤独 overcome loneliness.</p>
<p>【参考答语】</p>
<p>A: Do you ever feel lonely? I do feel lonely sometimes. It’s not a good feeling.</p>
<p>B: Yes, I know the feeling. Sometimes, even if not alone, I will often feel lonely, but I project my appearance was all okay. Perhaps, because of in the face of unknown future, a sense of helplessness and confusion always come to me.</p>
<p>A: In today’s busy world, many people suffer from loneliness. I’m hoping that I can share some positive advises that has helped me, and may just help you too. My proposal is to participate in various interest groups, such as dancing, writing, singing, sports etc. Through talking and communicating to other members, we all gain by the interchange of ideas, the swapping of experiences and the discussion of future hopes and aspirations. </p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>B: I agree. We also need to give a vent to our feeling. Speak as much as possible to people who are empathetic. You may surprisingly find that there are indeed different situations that we all have to deal with, however, we all share a common human experience. We all feel the emotions of love, loneliness, fear, loss, and joy.</p>
<p>A: Yes that’s definitely true. </p>
<p>B: When you start to understand that other people have the same feeling with you, you can start to feel a lot closer to the outside. This is the way to begin to mend feelings of isolation and loneliness.</p>
<p>A: Yes, in this way we can regain more confidence and it could be easier for us to overcome any difficulties.</p>
<p>B: Anyway, to keep a positive attitude is the most important way.</p>
<p>A: I suddenly think of it, may be having a pet to care for is helpful to overcome lonely too. There are many benefits to owning a very loyal and loving pet such as a puppy or a cat.</p>
<p>B: Good idea.</p>
<p>以上，就是文都六级英语老师为各位考生带来的六级口语考试第八场的互动讨论部分，希望能够对各位考生有所助益。文都教育祝各位同学都可以取得令人满意的成绩。</p>
➜422万人报名，42万人弃考，这十分之一的比例……
http://www.sohu.com/a/433985256_100684	31388
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20201124/bcb90ba2af47420382ee650c636c30e0.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>考研进入复习备考关键时期，但不少同学觉得自己复习的效果差，老觉得自己考不上。</p>
<p>虽然考研大军千千万，但依然有不少同学放弃，坚持到最后你就赢了一半。我们来看一下《2020全国研究生招生调查报告》，一组关于“弃考率”的数据或许能让你不那么焦虑。</p>
<p><strong>考研弃考情况</strong></p>
<p>20考研弃考率超过10%</p>
<p>硕士研究生报考热度居高不下，不少地区及高校考研弃考率超过10%以上。</p>
<p><strong>先来看省份：</strong></p>
<p>广东省：2019年硕士研究生考试中，应考人数约14万人，实际参加考试的人数约12.4万人，弃考率达到约11%。</p>
<p>辽宁省：2019年硕士研究生考试应考人数为109539人，实际参加考试为97365人，缺考人数为12174人，弃考率约11%。</p>
<p><strong>再来看高校：</strong></p>
<p>北京大学法学院：2019年报考人数大约4241人，弃考人数共计约1019人，弃考比例约24%；</p>
<p>上海财经大学：2019年网报14083人，实际参加考试12649人，弃考1434人，弃考率超过10%；</p>
<p>深圳大学：2019年网报确认16019人，实考14083人，弃考人数近2千人，弃考率达到12%。</p>
<p>20考研弃考率大约10%，也就是说，341万人报考，坚持到最后走出考场的只有300万左右。</p>
<p>按这个弃考率推算，21考研人数大约420多万，能坚持到最后的或许只有378万，也就是说弃考人数预计在42万人！</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
